          "Hirschsprung disease shows absence of ganglion cells in affected colon segment",
          "Parkinson's disease often presents with constipation before motor symptoms",
          "Post-infectious IBS results from inflammation-induced ENS damage"
        ],
        mnemonics: {
          "ENS plexuses": "My Submucosal friend - Myenteric controls Motility, Submucosal controls Secretion",
          "Peristaltic reflex": "Push Distally, Relax - Proximal contracts, Distal relaxes when bolus approaches",
          "Major inhibitory transmitters": "NO VIP in the gut - Nitric Oxide and VIP are main inhibitory signals"
        }
      },
      textbookRefs: [
        { textbook: "Guyton & Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology", edition: "14th", chapter: "Chapter 63 - General Principles of Gastrointestinal Function" }
      ],
