          presentation: "A 28-year-old develops chronic abdominal pain, bloating, and diarrhea 6 months after severe gastroenteritis. Colonoscopy and labs are normal.",
          clinicalPearl: "Gut infection can damage enteric neurons, leading to persistent ENS dysfunction. This explains why some patients develop IBS after infectious gastroenteritis.",
